.TH WJ 1 "2026" "wj 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wj \- cross-project daily task & time tracker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wj
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ args ]
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wj
tracks what you work on across every project from one command line. Each
action appends to an immutable per-day TSV event log; status tables, the
schedule grid, the multi-day gantt, reports and exports are all
.I derived
by replaying that log, so your data stays plain, greppable and easy to analyse.
.PP
The project is auto-detected from the git remote, falling back to the repository
folder name, then to
.IR default_project .
Run with no command to show today's status (or launch the UI when
.I interface
is set to
.IR ui ).
.SH TASK COMMANDS
.TP
.BI "start " desc
Begin a new task; it gets the next id (T1, T2, ... per day). Auto-pauses any
running task in the same project.
.TP
.BI "pause " "[id] [why]"
Pause the running task (or the given id). Stops its clock.
.TP
.BI "resume " [id]
Resume the most-recent paused/deferred task (or the given id).
.TP
.BI "complete " [id]
Finish a task: sum its time and, in a git repo, record the commits made during
its window.
.TP
.BI "defer " "[id] [why]"
Set a task aside (blocked, or to pick up another day).
.TP
.BI "log " note
Attach a timestamped note to the running task.
.TP
.BI "amend " "[id] desc"
Replace a task's description (running task, or given id). Appends an event;
never rewrites history.
.TP
.BI "move " "[id] proj"
Re-home a task to another project (fix wrong auto-detection).
.TP
.BI "cancel " [id]
Void a mistaken task: 0 time, hidden from status/grid/report (kept in the raw
log for audit).
.SH VIEW & ANALYSIS
.TP
.B ls
List currently-open tasks. Today by default;
.B --days N
scans the last N days.
.TP
.BI "show " id
Full timeline of one task. Today by default;
.B --date
for a past day.
.TP
.BI "status " [date]
Per-task totals table for a day (default: today). The default command.
.TP
.BI "grid " [date]
Slot-by-slot schedule for a day.
.TP
.B gantt
Multi-day overview: rows (\fB--by\fR project|task) by days of tracked time.
Default range: the last 7 days through \fB--to\fR.
.TP
.B report
Aggregate time across a date range, grouped by \fB--by\fR.
.TP
.B export
Dump raw events as csv / json / tsv over a date range.
.PP
The read views
.RB ( status ", " ls ", " show ", " grid ", " gantt )
also accept
.B --json
for a stable machine-readable contract \(em this is what the UI front-end consumes.
.SH OTHER
.TP
.B ui
Launch the wj-tui front-end (requires the
.B wj-tui
binary). A bare
.B wj
launches it too when
.I interface=ui
in the config.
.TP
.B config
Print the path to the active config file.
.TP
.BI "completion " SHELL
Print a completion script:
.B completion bash
or
.BR "completion zsh" .
.TP
.B version
Print the wj version (also \fB--version\fR, \fB-V\fR).
.TP
.B help
Show the built-in help.
.SH FLAGS
.TP
.BI "--at " TIME
Act at a past time instead of now. Flexible format: 9, 930, 0930, 9:30, 9.30,
9am, 9pm, 9:30pm all normalise to HH:MM.
.TP
.BI "--date " YYYY-MM-DD
Act on another day (alias \fB--on\fR). Combine with \fB--at\fR to reconstruct a
past day; defaults the day for status/grid.
.TP
.BI "--days " N
ls: how many days back to scan. Default 1 (today).
.TP
.BI "--project " NAME
Override project detection (e.g. for non-git work).
.TP
.BI "--from " D ", --to " D
Inclusive date range YYYY-MM-DD (report, export, gantt).
.TP
.BI "--by " KEY
Grouping: project | task | day (report); project | task (gantt).
.TP
.BI "--format " FMT
export format: csv | json | tsv. Default csv.
.TP
.B --json
Emit a machine-readable view (status, ls, show, grid, gantt).
.SH CONFIGURATION
Config lives at
.I ~/.config/wj/config
(seeded on first run; key=value, shell-sourced). Keys:
.IR shift_start ", " shift_end " (working-day bounds), "
.I slot_minutes
(grid step),
.I round
(down|nearest),
.I totals
(exact|slot),
.I default_project ", "
.I git_tag
(on|off), and
.I interface
(minimal|ui \(em the front-end for a bare
.BR wj ).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/wj/config
Settings (override with \fB$WJ_CONFIG\fR).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/wj/YYYY/MM/DD.tsv
The append-only event log (override with \fB$WJ_DATA_DIR\fR).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.nf
wj start "Refactor auth" --project backend
wj log "extracted token service"
wj pause
wj resume
wj complete
wj status
wj gantt --from 2026-06-01 --to 2026-06-07 --by project
wj export --format csv > june.csv
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
Full documentation and the optional terminal UI:
.UR https://github.com/Katestheimeno/wj
.UE
.SH AUTHOR
Katestheimeno
